description:
&lt;p&gt;Moorfields NHS Trust the leading provider of eye health services in the UK and a world class centre of excellence for ophthalmic research and education is looking to appoint a Divisional Manager to their Staff Bank to fulfil a full time ongoingrole in London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful, you must have the below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Graduate level qualification or equivalent experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extensive experience of management within an acute NHS environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of managing large budgets and the complexities of managing high numbers of staff across a variety of disciplines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Managing complex change&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding of the Health and Social care management environment and roles and responsibilities within it&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to develop strategy for the Health Economy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to assimilate &amp; co-ordinate various agendas prioritising appropriately&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Performance management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to Analyse highly complex information to support managerial decision making&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to make decisions in a multi- disciplinary environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advanced communication, presentation &amp; interpersonal skill&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High degree of report writing skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
